<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
Questionable status. A poorly known species which is frequently reported in ecological lists, but no recent descriptions exist (the newest being 
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, P." journalOrPublisher="Paul Lechevalier, Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Faune de France: Polychetes errantes" year="1923">Fauvel (1923)</bibRefCitation>
, who reproduces description and illustrations by 
<bibRefCitation author="Claparede, Edouard" journalOrPublisher="Memoires de la Societe de physique et d'histoire naturelle de Geneve" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="463 - 600" title="Glanures Zootomiques parmi les Annelides de Port-Vendres (Pyrenees Orientales)" volume="17" year="1864">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Claparède">Claparede</normalizedToken>
(1864)
</bibRefCitation>
). Fauvel considers the species very close to 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Syllidae" genus="Salvatoria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salvatoria clavata" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="clavata">Salvatoria clavata</taxonomicName>
(
<normalizedToken originalValue="Claparède">Claparede</normalizedToken>
, 1863) from which it differs in &quot; 
<taxonomicName lsidName="minor" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" rank="species" species="minor">minor</taxonomicName>
and variable characters&quot;. The species is not included in the treatise of the family by 
<bibRefCitation author="San Martin, G." journalOrPublisher="Fauna Iberica" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination=": 544 pp" title="AnnelidaPolychaeta II: Syllidae. In: Ramos MA, et al. (Eds)" volume="21, Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales, CA, SAIC, Madrid" year="2003">
San 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Martín">Martin</normalizedToken>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
. Type locality: Mediterranean (Port-Vendres, France).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
